orch-go is a CLI tool for orchestrating OpenCode sessions.

It provides commands for spawning new sessions, sending messages to existing
sessions, and monitoring session events via SSE.

Usage:
  orch-go [command]

Available Commands:
  abandon     Abandon a stuck or frozen agent
  account     Manage Claude Max accounts
  clean       List completed agents and optionally close their resources
  complete    Complete an agent and close the beads issue
  completion  Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
  daemon      Autonomous overnight processing
  doctor      Check health of orch services and optionally fix issues
  drift       Check if current work aligns with focus
  fetch-md    Fetch a URL and convert it to Markdown
  focus       Set or view the current north star priority
  handoff     Generate a session handoff document
  help        Help about any command
  history     Show agent history with skill usage analytics
  init        Initialize orch scaffolding in the current directory
  kb          Knowledge base commands for inline queries and artifact management
  learn       Review and act on system learning suggestions (delegates to kb learn)
  lint        Check CLAUDE.md files against token and character limits
  logs        View orch event logs
  monitor     Monitor SSE events for session completion
  next        Synthesize prioritized work recommendations
  patterns    Surface behavioral patterns for orchestrator awareness
  port        Manage port allocations for projects
  question    Extract pending question from an agent's session
  resume      Resume a paused agent with workspace-aware continuation
  retries     Show issues with retry patterns (failed attempts)
  review      Review agent work before completing
  send        Send a message to an existing session
  serve       Start the HTTP API server for the beads-ui dashboard
  servers     Manage development servers across projects
  sessions    Search and list OpenCode session history
  spawn       Spawn a new agent with skill context (default: headless)
  stale       Show stale beads issues (not updated recently)
  status      Show swarm status and active agents
  swarm       Batch spawn multiple agents with concurrency control
  synthesis   Synthesize recent activity from git, beads, and investigations
  tail        Capture recent output from an agent
  tokens      Show token usage for sessions
  transcript  Work with session transcripts
  usage       Show Claude Max usage limits
  version     Print the version information
  wait        Block until agent reaches specified phase
  work        Start work on a beads issue with skill inference

Flags:
  -h, --help            help for orch-go
      --server string   OpenCode server URL (default "http://127.0.0.1:4096")
  -v, --version         version for orch-go

Use "orch-go [command] --help" for more information about a command.
